{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Staphylococcus aureus pathogenicity islands (SaPIs) are highly mobile phage-related pathogenicity islands that typically carry genes for one or more superantigens. They are the primary cause of superantigen-induced diseases, especially toxic shock syndrome. SaPIs are induced to excise and replicate by the presence of a temperate phage. The SaPI then induces the phage to produce special small capsids into which it is encapsidated, resulting in exteremly high transfer frequences [[cite:PUB00056592]].</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This entry represents the SaPI CP3 protein, which is involved in the morphogenesis of the characteristic small SaPI capsids [[cite:PUB00056593]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF032437" "Uncharacterised conserved protein, UCP032437 type"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Encapsidation protein CP3", "short" "Encapsidation_CP3"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 2, "taxa" 30, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 60, "sets" 0, "proteins" 60, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 46}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR014570", :literature {"PUB00056592" {"URL" nil, "issue" "7", "authors" ["Tormo MA" "Ferrer MD" "Maiques E" "Ubeda C" "Selva L" "Lasa I" "Calvete JJ" "Novick RP" "Penades JR."], "ISO_journal" "J. Bacteriol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1128/JB.01349-07", "medline_journal" "J Bacteriol", "title" "Staphylococcus aureus pathogenicity island DNA is packaged in particles composed of phage proteins.", "year" 2008, "raw_pages" "2434-40", "volume" "190", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 18223072}, "PUB00056593" {"URL" nil, "issue" "1", "authors" ["Ubeda C" "Maiques E" "Tormo MA" "Campoy S" "Lasa I" "Barbe J" "Novick RP" "Penades JR."], "ISO_journal"